{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Mandatory minimum prison terms are costly and cruel. We must grasp this moment of consensus for reform....", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by former United States Atty Gen Eric H Holder Jr recounts story of Corey Jacobs, who has served 16 years of sentence of life without parole in federal prison for selling drugs; notes thousands of people in federal and state prisons are just like Jacobs, serving sentences wildly disproportionate to their crimes; underscores necessity of Congress taking action, particularly at time when there is bipartisan support for reforming criminal justice laws, especially those governing mandatory sentencing. ", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "6", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"lastname": "HOLDER", "rank": 1, "firstname": "Eric", "role": "reported", "organization": "", "middlename": "H."}], "original": "By ERIC H. HOLDER"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/14/opinion/sunday/eric-h-holder-mandatory-minimum-sentences-full-of-errors.html", "lead_paragraph": "Mandatory minimum prison terms are costly and cruel. We must grasp this moment of consensus for reform.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Sentences Full of Errors", "main": "Eric Holder: We Can Have Shorter Sentences and Less Crime", "content_kicker": "Opinion", "kicker": "Opinion"}, "_id": "57acd7e195d0e021d79802eb", "word_count": "1236", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2016/08/14/opinion/sunday/14holder/14holder-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2016/08/14/opinion/sunday/14holder/14holder-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 383, "url": "images/2016/08/14/opinion/sunday/14holder/14holder-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2016/08/14/opinion/sunday/14holder/14holder-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "383"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75,